## Task 3 Escalate JavaScript Overview

Objective: Write and execute basic JS programs.
JS is interpreted directly in the browser.
- Example program:
javascript
console.log("Hello, World!");
let age = 25;
if (age >= 18) { console.log("You are an adult."); }
else { console.log("You are a minor."); }
function greet(name) { console.log("Hello, " + name + "!"); }
greet("Bob");
Use Chrome Console (Ctrl+Shift+I → Console tab) to run JS code.
- Example addition program:
javascript
let x = 5; let y = 10; let result = x + y;
console.log("The result is: " + result);

